properties.headline: FLOODING - GUNNEDAH TO BOGGABRI Kamilaroi Highway between Mathias Road and Grantham Street West
properties.adviceB: Never drive through floodwater
properties.otherAdvice:
Several other local roads in the area may be closed or affected by flooding. Please visit the Gunnedah Shire Council website for current conditions on local roads.

The highway is also affected between Boggabri and Narrabri. Motorists should consider using an alternative route where possible.
properties.diversions:
All vehicles can use the following alternative route, via Coonabarabran.

Southbound: Newell Hwy then Oxley Hwy.
Northbound: Oxley Hwy then Newell Hwy.

Heavy vehicles will continue to use the Bloomfield St bypass to access the Oxley Hwy diversion.

properties.headline: FLOODING - WEE WAA TO NARRABRI Kamilaroi Highway between Purcell Avenue AND Newell Highway
properties.adviceB: Allow extra travel time; 	Never drive through floodwater
properties.diversions:
Eastbound: From Walgett; Gwydir Hwy to Moree and Newell Hwy to Narrabri.
Westbound: Newell Hwy to Moree and Gwydir Hwy to Walgett.

These diversions are suitable for all vehicles. Please note there is a load limit on the Grawan Creek Bridge east of Collarenebri. Traffic controllers are on site restricting heavy vehicles to one vehicle over the bridge at a time to allow all vehicles to pass.

properties.headline: FLOODING - IVANHOE TO WILCANNIA Cobb Highway
properties.adviceB: Exercise caution; 	Never drive through floodwater
properties.diversions:
Northbound: From Hay; Mid Western Hwy to Goolgowi, Kidman Way to Cobar, then Barrier Hwy to Wilcannia.

Southbound: From Wilcannia; Barrier Hwy to Cobar, Kidman Way to Goolgowi, then Mid Western Hwy to Hay.

This diversion is suitable for all vehicles and will add around 3 hours to your travel time.
